WEBVTT

00:02.219 --> 00:03.394
-PREVIOUSLY ON "OUTSIDERS"...

00:03.525 --> 00:04.656
-ELON! ELON!

00:04.787 --> 00:06.006
-I'M YOUR ONLY SON NOW.

00:06.136 --> 00:07.572
SO I'M GONNA BEAT THAT BOY
TOMORROW.

00:07.703 --> 00:09.661
-IF YOU LOSE, YOU'RE NOT MY SON
NO MORE.

00:09.792 --> 00:12.142
[ ENGINE REVS ]
[ CHEERING ]

00:12.273 --> 00:13.622
-OHH!

00:13.752 --> 00:16.625
-PROPHECY SAY THE RETURNED ONE
WILL BE BREN'IN.

00:16.755 --> 00:18.888
I DO NOT GIVE YOU MY STAFF
THIS FIRSTNIGHT.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.933
-WHAT'S RIGHT MINE,
I GOT A RIGHT TO TAKE.

00:21.064 --> 00:24.241
-[ GRUNTS ]
-I AM THE ONE NOW.

00:24.372 --> 00:26.461
-ME AND LIL FOSTER ARE NOT
MARRIED, LIKE I SAID.

00:26.591 --> 00:28.811
-THERE'S SOME THINGS I NEED
TO SAY TO YOU, G'WIN.

00:28.941 --> 00:30.639
-MAYBE IT'S TIME
YOU GO BE WITH HIM AGAIN.

00:30.769 --> 00:32.902
-YEAH, NOW THAT THE MINING
PERMIT'S FINALLY GONE THROUGH,

00:33.033 --> 00:35.035
WE NEED THEM OFF OUR LAND,
AND NOW.

00:35.165 --> 00:36.297
-SALLY-ANN,
YOU WANNA DO SOMETHIN'?

00:36.427 --> 00:37.820
-YOU GOT ANY MONEY?

00:37.950 --> 00:39.343
-THAT'S THE BEST BATCH
OF FARRELL WINE EVER,

00:39.474 --> 00:41.041
IF I DO SAY SO MYSELF.
-HOW MUCH?

00:41.171 --> 00:42.303
-[ CHANTING ] CHUG! CHUG! CHUG!

00:42.433 --> 00:43.782
-HAVE YOU BEEN DRINKING?
-[ VOMITS ]

00:43.913 --> 00:45.045
-TYLER. [ GRUNTING ]

00:45.175 --> 00:46.872
-WHAT IF
IT WASN'T JUST MOONSHINE?

00:47.003 --> 00:49.658
MAYBE THE FARRELLS ARE COOKING
SOMETHING NASTY UP THERE.

00:49.788 --> 00:51.790
AND IF THAT WERE TRUE,
NOT TOO MANY FOLKS AROUND HERE

00:51.921 --> 00:53.227
WOULD OPPOSE YOUR EVICTION
OF THEM.

00:53.357 --> 00:55.316
-I NEED YOU TO FIND ME
THAT SHINE HE DRUNK.

00:55.446 --> 00:57.796
-I SO MUCH AS HEAR YOU BREATHED
A WORD TO ONE OF THEM AGAIN,

00:57.927 --> 01:00.060
AND I BUST YOUR ASS.

01:03.106 --> 01:07.632
[ TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ]
-[ BREATHING SOFTLY ]

01:07.763 --> 01:10.548
[ TV CONTINUES ]

01:36.966 --> 01:40.143
[ TV CONTINUES
PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ]

01:50.545 --> 01:52.199
[ ANIMAL HOWLS IN THE DISTANCE ]

01:52.329 --> 01:54.984
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

02:04.036 --> 02:05.386
-[ EXHALES ]

02:24.927 --> 02:26.146
[ KISSES ]

02:27.582 --> 02:29.888
WE ALL LOVE YOU.

02:30.019 --> 02:31.716
[ KISSES ]

02:34.589 --> 02:35.981
[ WATER DRIPPING ]

02:43.815 --> 02:46.644
[ WATER DRIPPING ]

02:46.775 --> 02:50.431
♪♪

02:50.561 --> 02:54.609
-♪ THE DAWN IS UP, THERE'S
FIRE ON THE MOUNTAIN ♪

02:54.739 --> 02:58.656
♪ THEY'LL HAVE TO ANSWER
FOR THEIR CROOKED PLAN ♪

02:58.787 --> 03:01.746
♪ THE HOLLOWS
WILL SURROUND THEM ♪

03:01.877 --> 03:04.096
♪ AND THEY'LL GO RUNNIN'

03:04.227 --> 03:07.491
♪ BACK TO THE WRETCHED REALM
THEY CAME ♪

03:09.711 --> 03:16.152
♪ NOR WILL THE DOGS OF HELL
REFRAIN ♪

03:16.283 --> 03:21.810
♪ AND THE LAND WILL SUFFER
THOSE WHO PAID ♪

03:29.426 --> 03:30.819
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

03:42.004 --> 03:44.006
-[ SIGHS ]

03:50.534 --> 03:52.232
[ EXHALES ]

04:01.806 --> 04:03.199
[ GROANS ]

04:04.505 --> 04:07.421
[ SIGHS ] HEY, CALEB.

04:09.510 --> 04:11.163
CALEB?

04:14.645 --> 04:16.256
CALEB?

04:20.608 --> 04:23.350
[ SIGHS ] HI.

04:25.265 --> 04:26.788
[ SIGHS ]

04:26.918 --> 04:28.920
YOU, UH, YOU READY TO GO
TO SCHOOL?

04:33.490 --> 04:36.101
HERE. I'LL DO IT FOR YOU.

04:36.232 --> 04:38.626
[ DISTORTED CHATTERING ]

04:41.933 --> 04:43.761
-[ EXHALES ]

04:43.892 --> 04:45.502
[ RAGGED BREATHING ]

04:45.633 --> 04:48.070
[ DISTORTED SHOUTING ]

04:48.200 --> 04:50.768
[ SHOUTING CONTINUES, LOUDER ]

04:51.987 --> 04:53.684
-HELL YEAH! YOU'RE MINE!

04:53.815 --> 04:56.557
YEAH, YOU'RE GOING DOWN!
[ LAUGHS ] WHOO!

04:56.687 --> 05:00.082
[ SHOUTING CONTINUES ]

05:06.001 --> 05:08.308
-[ GRUNTS, GASPS ]

05:08.438 --> 05:10.484
[ SHOUTING, CHEERING ]

05:10.614 --> 05:13.138
-[ LAUGHS ]
-OHH!

05:13.269 --> 05:15.576
[ CHEERING, LAUGHTER ]

05:20.798 --> 05:22.496
-THAT-A-BOY!

05:22.626 --> 05:25.325
[ PLAYING BLUEGRASS MUSIC ]

05:25.455 --> 05:29.851
-[ SINGING INDISTINCTLY ]

05:29.981 --> 05:32.070
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

05:32.201 --> 05:37.728
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

05:37.859 --> 05:40.383
♪♪

05:40.514 --> 05:42.516
-HE'S LOOKING AT YOU...

05:42.646 --> 05:44.256
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

05:46.998 --> 05:50.524
FINELY DONE, COUSIN,
I MUST SAY.

05:51.916 --> 05:53.353
COME ON. THE PITFIGHT.

05:53.483 --> 05:54.789
-OH. [ LAUGHS ]

05:54.919 --> 05:56.530
-NOBODY THOUGHT
YOU HAD IT IN YOU.

05:56.660 --> 05:58.532
-ME NEITHER.

05:58.662 --> 06:00.447
-YOU KNOW, UH...

06:02.753 --> 06:04.538
THEY ALWAYS TOLD ME

06:04.668 --> 06:07.497
THE WORLD DOWN THERE
WAS NO GOOD.

06:07.628 --> 06:08.933
THEY'D GONE
AND THEY'D LOST EVERYTHING

06:09.064 --> 06:10.413
THAT MADE LIFE WORTH LIVING.

06:10.544 --> 06:12.110
BUT ME AND YOU, WE KNOW
THAT AIN'T ALL TRUE.

06:12.241 --> 06:13.982
-OH, WE DO?

06:16.288 --> 06:18.465
-I'M HASIL.

06:18.595 --> 06:20.075
YOU'RE THE READER.

06:20.205 --> 06:21.859
YEAH, YOU'RE THE READER.

06:21.990 --> 06:23.383
HOW'D YOU DO IT?

06:23.513 --> 06:26.386
-I MET A GUY DOWN THERE --
WORKED AT THE NEWSPAPER.

06:26.516 --> 06:28.126
OFFERED TO HELP ME.

06:28.257 --> 06:30.564
GOT IN LOTS OF TROUBLE FOR IT,
IF I REMEMBER RIGHT.

06:30.694 --> 06:31.826
-YEAH, TROUBLE.

06:31.956 --> 06:35.003
I HEAR TROUBLE, COUSIN.

06:35.133 --> 06:38.833
-DON'T LOOK NOW, BUT THAT
FAIR-HAIRED ONE OVER THERE

06:38.963 --> 06:41.531
HAS BEEN STARING AT YOU ALL DAY.

06:41.662 --> 06:44.229
-ALL RIGHT.

06:44.360 --> 06:46.231
PLEASURE KNOWING YOU, MR. ASA.

06:46.362 --> 06:47.624
WELCOME BACK.

06:47.755 --> 06:49.887
-THANK YOU.

06:50.018 --> 06:52.368
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

06:52.499 --> 06:54.805
-TOOK SOME SHINE,
SOLD IT DOWNTOWN.

06:54.936 --> 06:56.459
FOSTER TOOK EXCEPTION.

07:00.289 --> 07:02.378
GED-GEDYAH!

07:02.509 --> 07:03.771
-GED-GEDYAH.
[ JARS CLINK ]

07:03.901 --> 07:06.948
WHOA. [ CHUCKLES ]

07:08.340 --> 07:11.213
-LADIES, GED-GEDYAH.

07:11.343 --> 07:13.128
-GED-GEDYAH.
-GED-GEDYAH.

07:13.258 --> 07:15.435
-GIRL'S NAME IS
BARBARA McGINTUK,

07:15.565 --> 07:17.567
BUT SHE'S A SHAY.

07:17.698 --> 07:21.310
HER GRANDMOTHER MARRIED
MY GREAT-AUNT'S HUSBAND.

07:21.441 --> 07:24.226
YOU CAN ASK HER YOURSELF.

07:24.356 --> 07:26.358
-I KNOW YOU'D BEEN GONE
A LONG TIME.

07:26.489 --> 07:28.665
I JUST WANTED TO WELCOME YOU.

07:28.796 --> 07:30.580
-THANK YOU.

07:30.711 --> 07:32.277
-WE'LL GET YOU A WAISTCOAT, TOO.

07:32.408 --> 07:34.323
I HAVE AN UNCLE
GOT A DOZEN OF THEM,

07:34.454 --> 07:36.499
AND I'M SURE HE CAN SPARE ONE.

07:36.630 --> 07:39.937
TRUTH IS, YOU LOOK TERRIBLE.

07:40.068 --> 07:42.200
SO NOW...

07:42.331 --> 07:45.029
YOU HAVE TO DANCE WITH ME.

07:45.160 --> 07:46.727
-I DO?

07:46.857 --> 07:49.338
-A GIRL GIVES YOU A GIFT,
YOU GOTTA ASK HER TO THE FLOOR.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.471
COME ON, BOY, THIS WAY.

07:51.601 --> 07:52.820
-OKAY.

07:52.950 --> 07:55.387
-♪ HE WALKED DOWN THE TRACK

07:55.518 --> 07:57.172
♪ BUT HE DIDN'T GO ON BACK

07:57.302 --> 08:00.915
♪ HE LAID DOWN HIS SABER
AND DIED, LORD, LORD ♪

08:01.045 --> 08:04.135
♪ HE LAID DOWN HIS SABER
AND DIED ♪

08:04.266 --> 08:07.269
[ SONG ENDS, CHEERING ]

08:08.531 --> 08:11.926
[ SLOW SONG PLAYING ]

08:14.406 --> 08:16.800
-[ WHISPERS INAUDIBLY ]

08:27.942 --> 08:32.686
♪♪

08:41.303 --> 08:43.348
-LOOKS LIKE YOU HAVEN'T
FORGOTTEN EVERYTHING,

08:43.479 --> 08:44.915
ASA FARRELL.

08:45.046 --> 08:47.222
-WHY, THANK YOU.

08:49.659 --> 08:52.227
-SEE IF YOU REMEMBER THIS ONE.

08:56.840 --> 08:59.626
-[ GRUNTS ]
[ LAUGHTER ]

08:59.756 --> 09:01.671
[ MUSIC STOPS,
LAUGHTER CONTINUES ]

09:01.802 --> 09:06.763
-[ GRUNTING ]
[ APPLAUSE ]

09:06.894 --> 09:08.286
[ EXPLOSION ]

09:11.420 --> 09:13.291
[ EXPLOSION ]

09:13.422 --> 09:16.381
[ CHAIN SAWS REV ]

09:24.868 --> 09:26.566
[ EXPLOSION ]

09:28.306 --> 09:30.221
-WHAT THE HELL THEY THINK
THEY'RE DOING?

09:30.352 --> 09:31.701
[ EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE ]

09:31.832 --> 09:33.964
-EXTENDING THE OLD LOGGING ROAD,
IT LOOKS LIKE.

09:34.095 --> 09:37.185
-YEAH, THE ONE THAT
WE BLOCKED UP YEARS AGO.

09:37.315 --> 09:39.056
[ SIGHS ]

09:39.187 --> 09:40.928
-FOSTER, WHERE YOU GOING?

09:41.058 --> 09:42.494
-WHERE YOU THINK?
-LISTEN TO ME.

09:42.625 --> 09:43.931
YOU TAKE ONE SHOT AT THEM,

09:44.061 --> 09:45.541
AND THEY WILL COME AT US
WITH EVERYTHING THEY GOT.

09:45.672 --> 09:48.500
-GOOD.

09:48.631 --> 09:50.590
THEN THEY'LL KNOW
A FARRELL DON'T RUN.

10:09.260 --> 10:12.263
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

10:25.929 --> 10:27.539
-MISS...

10:32.196 --> 10:35.243
LISTEN, WE CAN KEEP DOING THIS
ALL DAY, JANE --

10:35.373 --> 10:38.289
OR WHATEVER YOU'RE
CALLING YOURSELF THESE DAYS.

10:39.943 --> 10:41.815
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?
-WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT I WANT.

10:41.945 --> 10:43.468
I GOTTA GET YOU
TO MOVE ON OUT OF HERE

10:43.599 --> 10:46.254
OR I'M TAKING YOU WITH ME,
AND THAT'S YOUR CHOICE.

10:46.384 --> 10:48.691
-UH, REALLY, CHIEF?
YOU KNOW TIMES ARE SO TOUGH.

10:48.822 --> 10:51.651
THIS LITTLE ITTY BITTY STRIP
HERE IS ALL I GOT.

10:51.781 --> 10:53.261
YOU KNOW? YOU FEEL ME?

10:53.391 --> 10:56.090
-YOU KNOW THIS IS MY JOB,
AND THAT'S ALL I GOT, TOO.

10:56.220 --> 10:57.744
SO I GOTTA -- I GOTTA DO
WHAT I GOTTA DO.

10:57.874 --> 11:00.572
-OKAY, THEN YOU JUST GO
AND YOU TAKE ME IN, SHERIFF.

11:00.703 --> 11:03.314
THERE'S NOTHING I CAN SAY
ABOUT IT.

11:03.445 --> 11:05.708
-MA'AM, I'M GONNA ASK YOU TO
TAKE YOUR HANDS OUT OF THERE.

11:05.839 --> 11:07.754
-MM-HMM.
I'M JUST LOOKING FOR MY I.D.

11:07.884 --> 11:10.582
YOU KNOW, SO YOU CAN GO ON
AND -- AND -- AND BOOK ME,

11:10.713 --> 11:12.019
YOU KNOW?

11:12.149 --> 11:14.195
OH -- OH -- OH -- THERE IT IS.

11:14.325 --> 11:16.110
LOOK THERE. GOT MY NAME ON IT.

11:16.240 --> 11:17.894
-YOU THINK YOU'RE BEING
GODDAMN FUNNY?

11:18.025 --> 11:20.070
-WELL, I DON'T KNOW, SHERIFF.
YOU DO SEEM A LITTLE TENSE,

11:20.201 --> 11:21.376
YOU KNOW?

11:21.506 --> 11:22.725
-WELL, YOU KEEP
SASSING ME, MA'AM,

11:22.856 --> 11:25.249
YOU'RE GONNA SEE ME TENSE.

11:26.816 --> 11:30.820
HEY. HEY, I'M TALKING TO YOU.
YOU COME BACK HERE RIGHT NOW!

11:41.918 --> 11:43.790
-THEY'RE BLOWING UP
THAT WHOLE RIDGE.

11:43.920 --> 11:45.661
THAT MEANS HALF OUR WATER
GOES BAD.

11:45.792 --> 11:48.708
-AS I SAID,
IT AIN'T GONNA HAPPEN.

11:48.838 --> 11:51.101
BHRADAIN,
GO AROUND TO MORNINGSIDE

11:51.232 --> 11:53.756
AND YOU TELL THE McGINTUK BOYS
WHAT TRANSPIRED.

11:53.887 --> 11:55.366
THEY PROBABLY HEARD NOTHING
OVER THERE.

11:55.497 --> 11:56.977
LET'S SEE HOW MUCH FIRE
YOU CAN GET FROM THEM.

11:57.107 --> 11:58.543
-YES, SIR. IT'S DONE.

11:58.674 --> 12:00.807
-NO, FOSTER, THAT'S A MISTAKE.
YOU KNOW IT IS.

12:02.939 --> 12:04.636
LAST TIME THEY STARTED
ON THAT ROAD, WHAT HAPPENED?

12:04.767 --> 12:07.509
-[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU WEREN'T EVEN BORN YET.

12:07.639 --> 12:09.990
-NO, BUT I HEARD THE STORY
SINCE I WAS A GIRL.

12:10.120 --> 12:11.905
TWO OF OUR PEOPLE GOT SHOT
BY THE POLICE.

12:12.035 --> 12:14.603
ONE OF THEM WAS YOUR FA.
HE WAS OUR BREN'IN.

12:16.474 --> 12:18.868
-AND WHAT HAPPENED AFTER THAT?

12:18.999 --> 12:22.132
HUH? WHAT COME UP THAT ROAD?

12:22.263 --> 12:23.568
I'LL TELL YOU.

12:23.699 --> 12:26.136
NOBODY, 'CAUSE THEY STOPPED
CUTTING IT.

12:26.267 --> 12:29.096
THEY WENT AWAY,
AND THAT IS WHAT HAPPENED.

12:29.226 --> 12:31.054
-WELL, IT WAS TOO HIGH A PRICE.

12:31.185 --> 12:33.404
-FOSTER, HEAR ME OUT, PLEASE.

12:33.535 --> 12:36.756
LOOK, I REMEMBER YOUR FA.
I WAS 4 YEARS OLD WHEN HE DIED.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.801
THE MAN WAS A GIANT.

12:38.932 --> 12:42.239
NOW I HONOR HIS LEGEND,
BUT... [ SIGHS ]

12:42.370 --> 12:44.764
WE CAN'T FIGHT THEM
LIKE WE USED TO.

12:44.894 --> 12:46.591
THAT'S WHAT THEY'RE HOPING
WE DO.

12:46.722 --> 12:48.158
WE SHOOT FIRST,

12:48.289 --> 12:49.769
GIVE THEM THE RIGHT
TO COME AT US WITH AN ARMY.

12:49.899 --> 12:51.945
AND IF WE DO THAT --
-YOU LISTEN TO ME, LOSTIE.

12:52.075 --> 12:54.469
THIS MOUNTAIN IS OURS,

12:54.599 --> 12:57.341
BUT IT DON'T COME FREE.

12:57.472 --> 13:00.736
WE GOTTA PAY RENT ON IT
LIKE ANYBODY.

13:00.867 --> 13:04.348
ONLY OUR RENT, IT COME IN BLOOD.

13:07.612 --> 13:11.747
BHRADAIN, GO.

13:11.878 --> 13:14.315
AND THE REST OF YOU,
YOU COME WITH ME.

13:23.019 --> 13:25.805
-YOU KNOW,
IF IT WEREN'T FOR YOU,

13:25.935 --> 13:28.459
WE WOULDN'T HAVE KNOWN ANY OF
THIS WAS COMING DOWN, ASA.

13:28.590 --> 13:31.723
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE OF US
THAT KNOWS THEM.

13:31.854 --> 13:33.900
SUPPOSE YOU HEAD BACK DOWN THERE
AND STRAIGHTEN THIS OUT.

13:34.030 --> 13:36.163
-THEY AIN'T GONNA LISTEN TO ME.

13:42.082 --> 13:43.344
SHIT.

13:46.913 --> 13:49.045
-YOU JUST GONNA SIT THERE?

13:51.178 --> 13:53.310
[ SCHOOL BELL RINGS ]

13:56.792 --> 13:59.882
-HEY, HOW'S SCHOOL TODAY?
YOU OKAY?

14:02.015 --> 14:05.105
I GOTTA TAKE YOU TO YOUR, UM,
AUNT LEDDA'S HOUSE, OKAY?

14:06.889 --> 14:09.631
WHAT'S THAT?

14:09.761 --> 14:11.589
HEY. WHAT'S THAT ON YOUR FACE?

14:11.720 --> 14:15.898
WHAT DID SOMEONE DO?
YOU GET SCRATCHED?

14:16.029 --> 14:17.944
HEY, YOU GET IN A FIGHT?

14:18.074 --> 14:20.990
-NO.

14:21.121 --> 14:24.689
-YOU HIT HIM BACK?
-I DIDN'T GET IN A FIGHT.

14:26.561 --> 14:28.128
-[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

14:32.915 --> 14:36.049
-KNOW SOMETHING?
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY TO YOU.

14:36.179 --> 14:38.442
-YOU ALREADY SAID IT WITHOUT
SAYING IT'S WHAT I'D SAY.

14:38.573 --> 14:41.402
-I CANNOT GO BACK DOWN THERE,
G'WIN, AND YOU KNOW IT.

14:41.532 --> 14:42.882
-DO I?

14:43.012 --> 14:45.014
-WHAT, YOU THINK I SPENT
SIX MONTHS IN THAT BOX

14:45.145 --> 14:46.886
BECAUSE, WHAT,
I WAS ENJOYING MYSELF?

14:47.016 --> 14:49.845
BECAUSE I DIDN'T CARE
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER?

14:49.976 --> 14:51.586
HUH?

14:51.716 --> 14:55.546
-NO. IT'S GOT TO BE SOME
OTHER THING, SOMETHING ELSE.

14:55.677 --> 14:58.680
-I WANNA BE HERE WITH YOU,
WITH ALL OF US.

14:58.810 --> 15:00.464
THAT'S IT. THAT'S THE REASON.

15:00.595 --> 15:01.901
-YOU'RE A GODDAMN LIAR.

15:02.031 --> 15:04.251
-HOW COME YOU NEVER GOT MARRIED
TO HIM?

15:07.080 --> 15:08.820
-YOU KNOW, YOU BELONG DOWN THERE
WITH THEM FAKERS,

15:08.951 --> 15:10.083
YOU PILE OF PIG SHIT.

15:10.213 --> 15:13.129
GO ON! RUN AWAY.

15:13.260 --> 15:14.826
-THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT
I'M NOT DOING.

15:14.957 --> 15:18.526
-HORSES. YOU'RE RUNNING
EVEN WHEN YOU'RE STANDING STILL.

15:18.656 --> 15:21.007
-OKAY.

15:21.137 --> 15:23.618
-OH, THAT WAS TOO EASY.

15:23.748 --> 15:25.533
OH, NO, KEEP WALKING,
ASA FARRELL.

15:25.663 --> 15:27.927
YOU RAN AWAY AND LEFT ME
10 YEARS AGO.

15:28.057 --> 15:29.276
YOU THINK YOU CAN
JUST COME BACK,

15:29.406 --> 15:31.060
DO YOUR TIME, WIN A PITFIGHT,

15:31.191 --> 15:32.366
AND WE ALL WELCOME YOU BACK
LIKE SOME KIND OF HERO?

15:32.496 --> 15:34.063
-I SAID I WAS SORRY.

15:34.194 --> 15:37.806
-YOU DID? I MUST'VE MISSED IT.

15:37.937 --> 15:39.242
-OKAY.

15:39.373 --> 15:41.331
I'M SAYING I'M SORRY NOW.

15:44.856 --> 15:47.381
-WHATEVER IT IS THAT YOU THINK
THAT WE HAVE UP HERE,

15:47.511 --> 15:49.774
IT'S GOING AWAY AND SOON.

15:49.905 --> 15:52.473
-OKAY, THEN...

15:52.603 --> 15:54.388
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

15:57.913 --> 16:00.960
-SHOW THEM WHO WE ARE.

16:04.050 --> 16:05.616
[ HAMMER CLICKS ]

16:05.747 --> 16:08.968
-SO WE GOT FIVE PISTOLS,
THREE NEW SHOTGUNS,

16:09.098 --> 16:10.230
PLUS THE SPRINGFIELDS

16:10.360 --> 16:11.622
AND THE RIFLE WE GOT
THE OTHER NIGHT.

16:11.753 --> 16:13.189
-MM.
[ GUN CLICKS ]

16:13.320 --> 16:14.451
FOUR PISTOLS.

16:14.582 --> 16:16.453
[ GUN THUDS ]

16:16.584 --> 16:19.848
WE NEED REPEATERS
IS WHAT WE NEED.

16:19.979 --> 16:22.068
AUTOMATICS.

16:22.198 --> 16:24.418
-MAKE THAT EIGHT PISTOLS, FA.

16:24.548 --> 16:27.116
I GOT FOUR MORE GOOD .44s
FROM DOWN IN SHAYTOWN.

16:27.247 --> 16:28.726
[ GUNS CLATTER ]

16:28.857 --> 16:30.946
THEN THERE'S THIS...

16:31.077 --> 16:34.384
REVENUERS' FIRE
FROM BACK IN PROHIBITION DAYS.

16:34.515 --> 16:35.995
-IT WORK?
-THINK SO.

16:36.125 --> 16:38.562
-OH, YOU THINK SO.

16:38.693 --> 16:40.477
YOU GOT ROUNDS FOR IT?

16:40.608 --> 16:42.001
-YEP.

16:48.703 --> 16:50.009
-THAT IT?

16:50.139 --> 16:52.533
AND YOU DON'T KNOW
IF IT SHOOTS OR NOT.

16:52.663 --> 16:54.926
-I-I DIDN'T WANT TO WASTE
ANY OF THE ROUNDS ON...

16:55.057 --> 16:57.190
-WELL, WHAT YOU'RE WASTING
IS MY TIME.

16:57.320 --> 16:58.887
YOU SEE A SIGN ON THE DOOR,

16:59.018 --> 17:00.497
SAY WE NEED GIRL CHILLUNS
IN HERE?

17:00.628 --> 17:02.456
-YOU TOLD US TO GET
ALL THAT WE COULD. I-I JUST --

17:02.586 --> 17:04.371
-YOU JUST WHAT?

17:04.501 --> 17:05.850
DIDN'T I TELL YOU

17:05.981 --> 17:08.027
NOT EVER SHOW YOUR FACE
AROUND HERE AGAIN?

17:09.680 --> 17:12.292
WHY YOU NO LISTEN
TO ANYTHING I SAY TO YOU?

17:12.422 --> 17:17.079
-I, UH, I KNOW A FELLA
THAT'S GOT SOME GOOD LONGBOWS.

17:17.210 --> 17:18.602
I'LL GO GET THEM.

17:18.733 --> 17:20.387
-COME ON. COME ON.

17:23.390 --> 17:24.695
-FA, PLEASE --

17:24.826 --> 17:28.438
-DON'T YOU EVER
CALL ME THAT AGAIN.

17:30.919 --> 17:33.704
-HE DIDN'T WIN FAIR.
-OH, YOU LOST.

17:33.835 --> 17:37.056
AND THAT'S WHAT I KNOW.
THAT'S WHAT EVERYBODY KNOWS.

17:37.186 --> 17:38.622
-WELL, LET ME PROVE IT TO YOU.

17:38.753 --> 17:41.843
-LOOK, I BELIEVED YOU BEFORE,

17:41.973 --> 17:46.195
AND THAT WAS THE LAST TIME.

17:46.326 --> 17:48.458
YOU WANT
TO COME BACK HERE AGAIN?

17:48.589 --> 17:53.463
THEN YOU DO SOMETHING RIGHT
FOR ME,

17:53.594 --> 17:55.422
FOR THIS FAMILY.

18:04.257 --> 18:07.086
[ DOOR OPENS, SLAMS ]

18:08.783 --> 18:12.178
[ DISTANT BIRD CAWING ]

19:17.373 --> 19:21.508
♪♪

19:46.446 --> 19:48.796
[ DOOR BELL CHIMES ]

19:48.926 --> 19:52.060
[ REGISTER BEEPS ]
-$4.99. THANK YOU.

19:52.191 --> 19:55.063
HAVE A NICE DAY.
-YOU, TOO.

19:55.194 --> 19:58.414
-HELLO.
-HELLO.

19:58.545 --> 20:00.982
[ Whispers ] APPLE.

20:01.112 --> 20:03.202
[ MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY
ON SPEAKERS ]

20:11.775 --> 20:13.212
-[ SIGHS ]

20:15.214 --> 20:16.650
-SORRY.

20:25.615 --> 20:28.052
-LOOK HERE.

20:28.183 --> 20:34.233
4-8-8-8-8-2-9.

20:34.363 --> 20:36.322
OKAY?
-AWESOME. GOT IT, THANK YOU.

20:36.452 --> 20:38.715
THAT'LL BE $3.69.

20:38.846 --> 20:40.369
THANK YOU.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.241
[ DOOR BELL CHIMES ]
HERE YOU ARE. HAVE A NICE DAY.

20:42.371 --> 20:45.113
♪♪

21:01.129 --> 21:02.478
-MR. ROURKE?

21:02.609 --> 21:05.568
[ TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ]

21:08.310 --> 21:10.834
MR. ROURKE, IT'S ME, ASA.

21:13.097 --> 21:16.318
I SAW THE NEWSPAPER WAS CLOSED.
WHAT HAPPENED?

21:16.449 --> 21:19.060
[ SPORTS BROADCAST PLAYING
ON TV INDISTINCTLY ]

21:19.190 --> 21:21.236
MR. ROURKE?

21:23.760 --> 21:25.153
-FINALLY.

21:25.284 --> 21:26.502
-[ CHUCKLES ]

21:26.633 --> 21:29.331
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT TOOK SO LONG.

21:29.462 --> 21:32.291
-WELL, I WAS AWAY OUT WEST.

21:32.421 --> 21:33.988
-HOT DIGGITY DAMN.

21:34.118 --> 21:36.382
NOW THAT'S WHAT I CALL
INTERESTING.

21:36.512 --> 21:37.774
-[ CHUCKLES ]

21:37.905 --> 21:39.950
-YOU GO FROM ONE TO ZERO,

21:40.081 --> 21:43.258
AND THEN BACK AGAIN,
AND WHAT DO YOU GOT?

21:44.999 --> 21:47.784
-MR. ROURKE.

21:47.915 --> 21:51.658
MR. ROURKE, YOU OKAY?

21:51.788 --> 21:55.705
-YOUR WORD IS YOUR WAND.

21:55.836 --> 21:57.490
ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

21:57.620 --> 22:01.189
-Woman on TV:
♪ AND THE ROCKETS RED GLARE

22:01.320 --> 22:03.670
-YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT, MR. ROURKE.

22:03.800 --> 22:06.586
-♪ BOMBS BURSTING IN AIR

22:06.716 --> 22:10.546
♪ GAVE PROOF
THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

22:10.677 --> 22:14.985
♪ THAT OUR FLAG
WAS STILL THERE ♪

22:15.116 --> 22:16.596
-I THINK WE MIGHT HAVE GOT THEM.

22:16.726 --> 22:18.815
GOOD JOB, RIGHT?

22:20.730 --> 22:22.471
SHERIFF HOUGHTON,
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

22:22.602 --> 22:25.953
-MS. BRYANT.
-OH, PLEASE. CLAIRE.

22:26.083 --> 22:29.260
-UM...I COULDN'T HELP
NOTICING YESTERDAY,

22:29.391 --> 22:31.393
I CAME IN TO PICK UP CALEB,

22:31.524 --> 22:34.135
AND, UM, HE HAD BIG SCRATCHES
ON HIS FACE.

22:34.265 --> 22:35.615
-I SAW THOSE, TOO, YEAH.

22:35.745 --> 22:38.879
-I JUST WANTED TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.

22:39.009 --> 22:41.316
-WELL, HE SAID HE FELL
IN THE WOODS.

22:41.447 --> 22:43.971
-YOU LET HIM GO IN THE WOODS?

22:44.101 --> 22:45.929
-NO, NO, NO, WE DON'T DO THAT.

22:46.060 --> 22:48.715
-AH. HMM.

22:48.845 --> 22:50.847
WELL...

22:50.978 --> 22:54.111
-HE CAME TO SCHOOL
WITH THE SCRATCHES ON HIS FACE.

22:54.242 --> 22:57.811
TECHNICALLY, I SEE A CHILD
COME IN LOOKING LIKE THAT,

22:57.941 --> 23:01.118
I'M SUPPOSED TO PICK UP
THE PHONE, BUT...

23:01.249 --> 23:03.817
I ASSUMED YOU ALREADY
KNEW ABOUT IT.

23:03.947 --> 23:05.384
-YEAH.

23:05.514 --> 23:09.300
UH, WHERE ARE YOU FROM?
YOU FROM BOSTON? D.C.?

23:09.431 --> 23:11.433
-HARTFORD.
-HARTFORD.

23:11.564 --> 23:14.958
UM, WELL, WE'RE SURE VERY LUCKY
TO HAVE YOU HERE.

23:20.834 --> 23:23.924
MY LITTLE BOY'S --
HE'S ALL THERE IS.

23:28.537 --> 23:31.453
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:38.591 --> 23:40.549
-GOOD EVENING, EVERYBODY.

23:40.680 --> 23:42.246
WELCOME TO OUR HEARING.

23:42.377 --> 23:45.685
I'M SHERIFF TOM WEINEKE,
AS MOST OF YOU KNOW.

23:45.815 --> 23:48.252
UH, IT'S GOOD TO SEE
SUCH NICE TURNOUT.

23:48.383 --> 23:51.299
[ CHUCKLES ]
SO, UM, AS Y'ALL KNOW,

23:51.430 --> 23:53.562
THE EXTRACTION PERMIT
FOR SHAY MOUNTAIN

23:53.693 --> 23:55.085
FINALLY WENT THROUGH.

23:55.216 --> 23:58.437
TONIGHT WE'LL BE HEARING
ARGUMENTS, PRO AND CON,

23:58.567 --> 24:00.134
CONCERNING THE RELOCATION

24:00.264 --> 24:03.311
OF THE HOMESTEADER FAMILY
WE CALL THE FARRELLS.

24:03.442 --> 24:05.835
MS. HAYLIE GRIMES
OF ONE PLANET RESOURCES.

24:05.966 --> 24:08.098
-THANK YOU, SHERIFF.

24:08.229 --> 24:09.578
MY NAME IS HAYLIE GRIMES,

24:09.709 --> 24:11.493
AND I'M THE NEW
COMMUNITY RELATIONS MANAGER.

24:11.624 --> 24:13.887
AND I'M JUST THRILLED
TO BE A PART OF THIS EFFORT

24:14.017 --> 24:17.325
TO CREATE JOBS
AND REVITALIZE THIS TOWN.

24:17.456 --> 24:19.327
OUR SHAY MOUNTAIN
EXTRACTION PROJECT

24:19.458 --> 24:20.937
WILL BRING HUNDREDS OF JOBS HERE

24:21.068 --> 24:23.287
AND REALLY GET THIS TOWN
BACK ON ITS FEET.

24:23.418 --> 24:24.941
BUT WE CAN'T DO THAT

24:25.072 --> 24:27.814
UNTIL THE PEOPLE WHO ARE
ILLEGALLY SQUATTING ON OUR LAND

24:27.944 --> 24:30.120
HAVE BEEN RELOCATED
TO MORE SUITABLE HOUSING.

24:30.251 --> 24:31.470
[ CROWD MURMURING ]

24:31.600 --> 24:33.733
I KNOW
THESE ARE DIFFICULT TIMES,

24:33.863 --> 24:36.257
BUT THE STATE HAS TOLD US
THAT UNTIL THEY'RE GONE,

24:36.387 --> 24:37.911
WE CAN'T BEGIN WORK,

24:38.041 --> 24:41.305
MEANING THE START DATE
FOR HIRING FULL-TIME POSITIONS

24:41.436 --> 24:43.525
HAS BEEN PUSHED.
-PUSHED TILL WHEN?

24:43.656 --> 24:45.353
-UNTIL ALL THOSE PEOPLE
HAVE BEEN MOVED.

24:45.484 --> 24:46.789
-AND HOW LONG'S THAT GONNA TAKE?

24:46.920 --> 24:49.139
-THAT'S UP TO
THE COUNTY SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT.

24:49.270 --> 24:50.663
-TO HELL WITH THEM FARRELLS!

24:50.793 --> 24:52.186
-THEY'VE BEEN HERE A LOT LONGER
THAN YOUR FAMILY!

24:52.316 --> 24:53.753
-SHUT UP ABOUT MY FAMILY, SUE!

24:53.883 --> 24:55.145
JUST 'CAUSE YOU MARRIED
ONE OF THEM.

24:55.276 --> 24:56.538
[ LAUGHTER ]
-ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

24:56.669 --> 24:57.974
NOW, EVERYBODY QUIET DOWN.
-LEAVE 'EM ALONE!

24:58.105 --> 24:59.367
-JUST -- JUST --
JUST QUIET DOWN.

24:59.498 --> 25:01.717
[ POUNDING ON DOOR ]

25:01.848 --> 25:03.110
-HEY, BUTCH,
I KNOW YOU'RE IN THERE!

25:03.240 --> 25:04.633
COME ON, OPEN THE DOOR!
[ TURNS OFF TV ]

25:04.764 --> 25:06.374
[ POUNDING CONTINUES ]

25:06.505 --> 25:07.680
-BUTCH, I KNOW YOU'RE IN THERE!

25:07.810 --> 25:09.029
COME ON, I JUST WANT
TO TALK TO YOU.

25:09.159 --> 25:11.901
[ POUNDING CONTINUES ]

25:12.032 --> 25:14.643
I MEAN WHAT I SAY, BUTCH.
OPEN THE GODDAMN DOOR.

25:14.774 --> 25:17.341
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
I'M COMING.

25:17.472 --> 25:19.343
-HEY. [ LAUGHS ] I'M SORRY.

25:19.474 --> 25:21.389
SORRY TO BOTHER YOU, BROTHER.

25:21.520 --> 25:23.478
UM...

25:23.609 --> 25:25.132
HELLO, MA'AM...

25:25.262 --> 25:26.829
SIR.

25:26.960 --> 25:28.744
UM, LOOK, I NEED THE REST
OF THAT CASH

25:28.875 --> 25:31.355
AND I'M GONNA NEED IT NOW.
-YOU NEED SOMETHING,

25:31.486 --> 25:33.401
YOU MIGHT WANT TO TRY
A FRIENDLIER APPROACH.

25:33.532 --> 25:34.837
JUST SAYING.

25:34.968 --> 25:36.404
-I AIN'T GOT YOUR MONEY, SON.

25:36.535 --> 25:37.840
I'M LAYING LOW AS IT IS
'CAUSE OF YOU.

25:37.971 --> 25:39.799
-WHAT YOU TALKING ABOUT
'CAUSE OF ME?

25:39.929 --> 25:41.322
COME ON, 'CAUSE OF ME?

25:41.452 --> 25:43.411
LOOK, I'M THE ONE
THAT'S GOT TROUBLE, NOT Y'ALL.

25:43.542 --> 25:47.763
-WELL, WORD IS YOUR SHINE CAUSED
SOME KID TO KILL HIS DAD.

25:47.894 --> 25:49.069
NOW HE'S LOCKED UP.

25:49.199 --> 25:51.114
AND HE WAS
ONE OF MY BEST CUSTOMERS.

25:51.245 --> 25:53.813
-OKAY, LISTEN.

25:53.943 --> 25:56.424
I NEED THAT MONEY
TO GO ON A DATE.

25:56.555 --> 25:57.686
-[ SCOFFS ]
-[ LAUGHS ]

25:57.817 --> 25:59.166
-ALL RIGHT, I NEED IT
TO GO ON A DATE.

25:59.296 --> 26:00.602
I GOT A GIRL.
SHE LIKES TO BE TREATED SPECIAL.

26:00.733 --> 26:02.822
YOU UNDERSTAND?
-HEY.

26:02.952 --> 26:04.606
-YEAH.

26:06.782 --> 26:08.131
[ RUSTLING ]

26:09.655 --> 26:11.047
-HEY!

26:11.178 --> 26:13.441
DON'T JUST SIT THERE.

26:15.269 --> 26:17.619
-OH, LOOK AT THAT. LOOK AT THIS.

26:17.750 --> 26:19.229
YOU STILL OWE ME HALF
FOR THIS ONE, TOO.

26:19.360 --> 26:20.579
-WELL, THEN GO ON AND TAKE IT!

26:20.709 --> 26:22.537
-LISTEN TO ME.
-HEY, EASE UP! [ GRUNTS ]

26:22.668 --> 26:26.193
-[ Whispers ] LISTEN. LISTEN.
I WANT THAT PAPER, BUTCH.

26:26.323 --> 26:29.413
-I TOLD YOU, I AIN'T GOT IT.

26:31.067 --> 26:32.373
UHH!

26:32.503 --> 26:34.810
-I TOLD YOU I WANT THAT PAPER,
BUTCH!

26:34.941 --> 26:36.290
-HEY! HEY!
-I TOLD YOU.

26:36.420 --> 26:39.075
-GO! HERE!

26:39.206 --> 26:41.121
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE!

26:41.251 --> 26:43.471
GO!

26:43.602 --> 26:46.387
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

26:50.913 --> 26:52.219
[ ANIMAL HOWLS ]

26:52.349 --> 26:54.090
-WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

26:54.221 --> 26:55.614
-I FOUND IT.

26:56.919 --> 26:59.313
BHRADAIN'S GOT A LEAKY ROOF.

26:59.443 --> 27:01.141
I'M GONNA GO HELP HIM FIX IT.

27:01.271 --> 27:02.621
-ONLY REASON YOU'RE SAYING THAT

27:02.751 --> 27:04.144
IS 'CAUSE YOU WANT ME TO KNOW
YOU'RE LYING.

27:05.928 --> 27:07.887
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

27:08.017 --> 27:09.889
-NOWHERE.

27:11.542 --> 27:14.458
-HERE.

27:14.589 --> 27:16.330
-I DON'T NEED THAT.

27:16.460 --> 27:18.419
-DON'T YOUR FA WANT
ALL THE FIRE HE CAN GET?

27:18.549 --> 27:19.812
MAKE A BIG SHOW
DOWN THE END OF THE ROAD?

27:19.942 --> 27:21.248
GET US ALL KILLED?

27:21.378 --> 27:23.293
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

27:23.424 --> 27:25.078
-FOSTER.

27:27.646 --> 27:31.214
ALL THAT DANCING, WITH HIM,

27:31.345 --> 27:34.130
DON'T MEAN NOTHING.

27:34.261 --> 27:37.351
-JUST IDLE TALK
WITHOUT THE TALK.

27:37.481 --> 27:40.528
-THAT'S RIGHT.

27:40.659 --> 27:43.313
-HMM.

27:43.444 --> 27:46.229
LISTEN...

27:46.360 --> 27:49.885
I KNOW YOU A LONG TIME.

27:50.016 --> 27:52.845
I KNOW HOW YOUR HEAD WORKS...

27:52.975 --> 27:56.631
ANDELSEWHERE.

27:56.762 --> 27:58.546
SO I KNOW YOU PLAN
ON DUSTING HIS BROOM,

27:58.677 --> 28:00.809
IF YOU HAVEN'T ALREADY.

28:04.465 --> 28:08.338
I'M JUST ASKING IF YOU LOVE ME
THE WAY THAT YOU SAY YOU DO...

28:15.519 --> 28:18.000
-AND I'M ASKING YOU

28:18.131 --> 28:20.916
TO THINK ABOUT
WHOSE SIDE YOU'RE ON --

28:21.047 --> 28:24.528
YOUR FA'S OR OURS.

28:37.411 --> 28:40.544
[ APPLAUSE ]

28:40.675 --> 28:42.198
-HEY, Y'ALL,
UM, I'M LEDDA DOBBS,

28:42.329 --> 28:43.983
AND, UH, AS Y'ALL PROBABLY KNOW,

28:44.113 --> 28:47.813
UM, MY HUSBAND, BREECE,
IS A MINER.

28:47.943 --> 28:49.858
AND HE'S OUT OF WORK.

28:49.989 --> 28:52.382
LOOK. I'M ALL FOR JOBS. I AM.

28:52.513 --> 28:56.778
BUT THESE MOUNTAINS, THEY --
THEY DON'T BELONG TO US.

28:56.909 --> 28:59.085
THEY BELONG TO GOD.

28:59.215 --> 29:03.089
AND -- AND WE'VE GOT NO RIGHT
TO BLOW THEM UP.

29:03.219 --> 29:04.743
-I NEED A JOB!
-NOW, THEY SAY THEY'RE --

29:04.873 --> 29:08.311
THEY'RE GONNA CREATE HUNDREDS
OF POSITIONS.

29:08.442 --> 29:11.488
BUT IF YOU ASK
ANY OF THOSE PEOPLE...

29:11.619 --> 29:13.882
[ CROWD MURMURING ]
...OVER IN KENLAYSON OR JUVILER,

29:14.013 --> 29:15.841
WHERE THEY --
THEY WRECKED THEIR WATER

29:15.971 --> 29:18.147
AND -- AND THEY FILLED THE AIR
WITH COAL DUST

29:18.278 --> 29:20.628
AND THE HOLLOWS
WITH BLACK SLUDGE.

29:20.759 --> 29:22.282
[ MURMURING INTENSIFIES ]
THEY WILL TELL YOU THAT

29:22.412 --> 29:25.372
MOST OF THE JOBS THAT THEY'RE
CREATING ARE OVERSEAS.

29:25.502 --> 29:27.156
-THAT IS NOT TRUE.
-IT IS TRUE.

29:27.287 --> 29:31.073
AND ONCE THEY'RE DONE POLLUTING
OUR TOWNS AND OUR SCHOOLS,

29:31.204 --> 29:35.121
THEY'LL TAKE THEIR BILLIONS
AND THEY'LL JUST GO BACK HOME

29:35.251 --> 29:40.213
AND THEY'LL LEAVE US WITH
OUR ILL HEALTH AND -- AND OUR --

29:40.343 --> 29:42.737
AND OUR STREAMS
WITH NO FISH IN THEM

29:42.868 --> 29:45.914
AND NOWHERE FOR OUR KIDS
TO PLAY.

29:46.045 --> 29:50.049
SO, LISTEN, I-I JUST --
I SAY LEAVE THEM FARRELLS BE,

29:50.179 --> 29:52.442
[ SCATTERED BOOING ]
AND MORE IMPORTANTLY,

29:52.573 --> 29:54.140
YOU LET THAT MOUNTAIN BE.

29:54.270 --> 29:57.186
[ SCATTERED APPLAUSE,
INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

30:02.757 --> 30:04.237
-MY NAME IS BREECE DOBBS.

30:04.367 --> 30:08.371
[ CHUCKLES ] LEDDA'S MY WIFE.

30:08.502 --> 30:10.809
WE AGREE ON SOME THINGS,

30:10.939 --> 30:14.116
AND WE DISAGREE ON OTHERS.

30:14.247 --> 30:15.988
WHERE WE AGREE,

30:16.118 --> 30:20.731
WE BOTH WANT TO RAISE OUR GIRLS
RIGHT AND GIVE THEM A FUTURE.

30:20.862 --> 30:22.995
BUT WE CAN'T DO THAT
WITHOUT WORK.

30:23.125 --> 30:24.823
[ CROWD AFFIRMING ]

30:24.953 --> 30:27.129
I COME OFF FROM MY SECOND TOUR
OF IRAQ AND I WORKED STEADY,

30:27.260 --> 30:30.872
BUT I AIN'T HAD A JOB
IN NEAR THREE YEARS NOW.

30:31.003 --> 30:32.918
-THAT'S TOUGH.
-AND THAT'S HARD.

30:33.048 --> 30:35.746
UM, BUT NOW THERE'S HOPE
FOR ME AND MY FAMILY

30:35.877 --> 30:38.140
AND ALL THE FAMILIES REPRESENTED
HERE TONIGHT 'CAUSE --

30:38.271 --> 30:39.838
-THAT'S RIGHT!
YOU SAID IT, BROTHER!

30:39.968 --> 30:41.187
[ APPLAUSE ]

30:41.317 --> 30:42.841
-THESE GOOD PEOPLE HERE,
THEY COME HERE

30:42.971 --> 30:46.627
AND THEY OFFER US JOBS SO WE CAN
HOLD OUR HEADS UP HIGH.

30:46.757 --> 30:49.108
YOU KNOW, BRING THIS TOWN BACK
FROM THE BRINK A LITTLE BIT.

30:49.238 --> 30:50.849
[ APPLAUSE ]

30:50.979 --> 30:54.504
THEM FARRELLS, THEY DON'T OWN
THAT LAND THEY LIVE ON.

30:54.635 --> 30:55.854
THEY GOT NO RIGHT
TO BE UP THERE.

30:55.984 --> 30:57.203
THEY DON'T PAY TAXES ON IT.

30:57.333 --> 30:58.857
THEY DON'T PUT THEIR KIDS
IN OUR SCHOOLS.

30:58.987 --> 31:00.641
-THAT'S RIGHT.
-THEY DON'T ABIDE BY OUR LAWS.

31:00.771 --> 31:02.904
SO I JUST GOT TO WONDER WHY...

31:03.035 --> 31:04.645
[ APPLAUSE, CHEERING ]
-BREECE!

31:04.775 --> 31:06.865
-WHY WE GOTTA PLAY BY THE RULES,
AND THEM FARRELLS DON'T.

31:06.995 --> 31:08.605
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
-ALL RIGHT, BREECE!

31:08.736 --> 31:11.391
-[ CHANTING ] BREECE! BREECE!

31:11.521 --> 31:13.480
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

31:13.610 --> 31:17.963
BREECE! BREECE! BREECE!

31:18.093 --> 31:21.357
-ALL RIGHT, JUST QUIET DOWN,
EVERYBODY. QUIET DOWN.

31:21.488 --> 31:24.665
-OH, SAY, CAN YOU SEE...

31:24.795 --> 31:28.190
BY THE DAWN'S EARLY LIGHT,

31:28.321 --> 31:30.758
WHEN SO LOUDLY WE CAVED

31:30.889 --> 31:34.762
AT THE FAT CAT'S LAST SCHEMING?

31:34.893 --> 31:38.244
WHOSE JAIL STRIPES
AND STRIP BARS

31:38.374 --> 31:41.421
THROUGH THE PALE URBAN BLIGHT,

31:41.551 --> 31:43.640
AND ALL THOSE POOR FOLKS
WE SQUASHED

31:43.771 --> 31:46.861
WERE SO GALLANTLY SCREAMING.

31:46.992 --> 31:49.864
AND THE DEEP POCKETS DID STARE,

31:49.995 --> 31:51.953
APLOMB NURSING THE DARE,

31:52.084 --> 31:54.695
AND IF YOU AIN'T RICH LIKE ME,

31:54.825 --> 31:57.741
THEN YOUR RIGHTS ARE
STRIPPED BARE.

31:57.872 --> 32:03.269
OH, SAY, DOES THAT
FAR-FANGLED BANNER AD DEPRAVE

32:03.399 --> 32:06.315
O'ER THE HOME OF PURE GREED

32:06.446 --> 32:08.970
AND THE LAND OF THE SLAVE?

32:13.801 --> 32:16.412
ANY OF YOU COME UP
THAT MOUNTAIN,

32:16.543 --> 32:19.720
YOU AIN'T GONNA BE
COMING BACK DOWN.

32:19.850 --> 32:22.636
THANK YOU.

32:22.766 --> 32:24.029
[ MICROPHONE CLATTERS ]

32:24.159 --> 32:25.508
-HEY, YOU THREATENING US?!

32:25.639 --> 32:27.206
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]
HUH?!

32:27.336 --> 32:29.773
GET BACK HERE, FARRELL!
YOU GET YOUR BUTT BACK HERE!

32:29.904 --> 32:31.471
I'M GONNA GET YOU!
-STOP.

32:31.601 --> 32:33.560
-GET OUT OF THE WAY, WADE!
-GET OUT OF THE WAY!

32:33.690 --> 32:35.779
-WHERE YOU GOING?

32:35.910 --> 32:39.218
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

32:39.348 --> 32:41.916
-COSTING US MONEY,
TELLING US WHAT TO DO?

32:42.047 --> 32:43.396
-THOSE FARRELLS!

32:43.526 --> 32:47.139
-POLICE ARE ON THE WAY,
JUST SO YOU KNOW.

32:47.269 --> 32:49.445
-I AIN'T DOING NOTHING.
I'M JUST WAITING FOR SOMEBODY.

32:49.576 --> 32:51.360
-YEAH, WELL,
YOU'RE SCARING PEOPLE OFF.

32:51.491 --> 32:55.364
[ SIREN WHOOPS ]

32:55.495 --> 32:57.062
DON'T SAY I DIDN'T WARN YOU.

32:57.192 --> 32:59.238
-HOW'S IT GOING TONIGHT?

32:59.368 --> 33:01.718
-WELL, IT'S, UH,
IT'S GOING PRETTY GOOD.

33:01.849 --> 33:04.156
-HE SAYS HE'S WAITING
FOR SOMEBODY.

33:05.548 --> 33:09.161
-WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

33:09.291 --> 33:10.466
-[ SCOFFS ]

33:10.597 --> 33:11.902
LOOK, DON'T A FELLA
HAVE THE RIGHT

33:12.033 --> 33:13.992
TO SIT OUTSIDE AND LOOK
AT THE STARS,

33:14.122 --> 33:15.906
LOOK AT THE MOON IN PEACE?

33:16.037 --> 33:17.691
-WELL, THIS IS PRIVATE PROPERTY,

33:17.821 --> 33:20.563
SO, UH, WHY DON'T YOU GO ON
ACROSS THE STREET OVER THERE?

33:20.694 --> 33:24.263
-WHY DON'T YOUMIND
YOUR OWN AFFAIRS, SIR?

33:24.393 --> 33:26.439
-COME ON. LET'S GO.
LET'S MOVE IT ALONG.

33:26.569 --> 33:29.659
-COME ON.
WHAT, YOU GONNA SHOOT ME?

33:29.790 --> 33:32.575
[ BATON CLICKS ]
[ LAUGHS ]

33:32.706 --> 33:35.143
-LET'S GO.

33:35.274 --> 33:38.407
COME ON, LET'S GO.

33:38.538 --> 33:42.020
I SAID LET'S GO.

33:42.150 --> 33:44.065
CAR 4 AT THE ACORN'S
ON CHAPEL STREET.

33:44.196 --> 33:45.414
I NEED SOME BACKUP.

33:45.545 --> 33:46.807
SHIT.
[ BATON CLATTERS ]

33:46.937 --> 33:48.243
YOU ARE UNDER ARREST.

33:48.374 --> 33:50.028
-[ LAUGHS ]
-STOP RIGHT THERE.

33:50.158 --> 33:51.899
I SAID STOP!

33:52.030 --> 33:56.034
I SAID STOP.
[ TASER CLICKING ]

33:56.164 --> 33:59.037
-[ GRUNTS ]

34:01.604 --> 34:03.519
-YOU THINK THAT GUY WAS
ONE OF THEM?

34:03.650 --> 34:05.043
OR ONE OF THOSE CRAZY-ASS
TREE HUGGER KIDS?

34:05.173 --> 34:06.609
[ CAN POPS ]
-I DON'T KNOW.

34:06.740 --> 34:08.916
COULDN'T TELL WHAT HE WAS.
-HE WAS ONE OF WHAT?

34:09.047 --> 34:10.265
WHAT HAPPENED?

34:10.396 --> 34:11.527
-WHERE'S CALEB?
IS HE -- HE SLEEPING?

34:11.658 --> 34:13.355
-I GUESS SO.

34:13.486 --> 34:15.009
-WE THINK THERE WAS A FARRELL
AT THE TOWN MEETING TONIGHT.

34:15.140 --> 34:16.228
-DAMN WEIRDO IS WHAT HE WAS.

34:16.358 --> 34:17.968
-HE WAS PRETTY SMART
FOR ONE OF THEM.

34:18.099 --> 34:19.622
-MR. GRANT TOLD US
IN HISTORY CLASS

34:19.753 --> 34:21.755
THAT THEY HAVE WHAT'S CALLED
SQUATTER'S RIGHTS.

34:21.885 --> 34:23.974
SAID WE TRIED TO KICK THEM OUT
A LONG TIME AGO,

34:24.105 --> 34:27.282
BUT TWO PEOPLE DIED.
-IT WASN'T THAT LONG AGO.

34:27.413 --> 34:29.154
YOUR UNCLE AND I WERE
LIKE CALEB'S AGE.

34:29.284 --> 34:31.199
-IT WASN'T TWO PEOPLE THAT DIED
NEITHER, SWEETIE.

34:31.330 --> 34:33.114
THERE WERE THREE.

34:35.029 --> 34:36.857
-[ SIGHS ]

34:36.987 --> 34:38.293
-MAN, HE'S OUT LIKE A LIGHT.

34:38.424 --> 34:40.426
-WELL, HE CAN
STAY HERE TONIGHT THEN.

34:40.556 --> 34:42.906
-JUST LIKE EVERY NIGHT.
-HEY.

34:44.691 --> 34:47.824
-UNCLE WADE, ARE YOU GONNA KICK
THE FARRELLS OFF THEIR LAND?

34:47.955 --> 34:50.088
-UH, WELL, EVICTING THEM IS --

34:50.218 --> 34:51.611
-ONE, IT'S NOT THEIR LAND.

34:51.741 --> 34:53.091
AND TWO,
IF YOU WERE DOING YOUR JOB,

34:53.221 --> 34:54.570
WE'D ALL BE A LOT BETTER OFF
BY NOW.

34:54.701 --> 34:56.050
-BREECE, WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO DO?

34:56.181 --> 34:57.747
-I WANT YOU TO DO SOMETHING,
ANYTHING.

34:57.878 --> 34:59.923
-WHAT DO YOU WANT ME --
DO YOU WANT ME TO GO UP THERE?

35:00.054 --> 35:03.666
-THAT'S WHAT COPS DO.
-I-I GOT A LITTLE BOY, BREECE.

35:03.797 --> 35:05.103
-I GOT TWO LITTLE GIRLS.
-YEAH, AND WHAT DO YOU THINK'S

35:05.233 --> 35:06.669
GONNA HAPPEN TO THEM?
-[ CLEARING THROAT ]

35:06.800 --> 35:08.062
-WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
TO THE WHOLE GODDAMN TOWN?

35:08.193 --> 35:09.542
EXCUSE ME, LEDDA.
-THE WHOLE GODDAMN TOWN

35:09.672 --> 35:10.978
HAS BEEN IN THE SHITTER
FOR 10 YEARS, SO...

35:11.109 --> 35:12.414
-YOU KNOW WHAT, BREECE?

35:12.545 --> 35:13.937
YOU'RE LIKE
A GODDAMN BROKEN RECORD, MAN.

35:14.068 --> 35:15.548
-HEY, I'LL BE
A GODDAMN BROKEN RECORD

35:15.678 --> 35:17.593
ALL I WANT IN MY OWN HOUSE.
YOU UNDERSTAND, WADE?

35:17.724 --> 35:19.639
-YOU KNOW THERE'S A PRECEDENT.
-OKAY. OKAY.

35:19.769 --> 35:21.858
THAT IS ENOUGH, BOTH OF YOU.
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

35:21.989 --> 35:24.861
[ RING, BEEP ]

35:24.992 --> 35:26.341
-YEAH?

35:29.518 --> 35:31.390
WHAT IN GOD'S NAME
DID YOU TASE HIM FOR?!

35:31.520 --> 35:33.435
[ CELL PHONE SNAPS SHUT ]

35:33.566 --> 35:36.830
♪♪

35:41.530 --> 35:44.533
♪♪

36:08.992 --> 36:10.690
-WHERE IS HE?
-UH, HE WON'T TELL US HIS NAME.

36:10.820 --> 36:13.040
AND OF COURSE,
HE DON'T HAVE AN I.D.

36:13.171 --> 36:15.042
UH, THERE'S A JUG OF SHINE
IN HIS BAG.

36:15.173 --> 36:16.348
YOU WANT ME TO HOLD IT?

36:16.478 --> 36:18.263
-NO. FILL OUT A FORM
FOR A JOHN DOE.

36:18.393 --> 36:19.699
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THIS.

36:33.756 --> 36:37.760
-HEY, DO I GET A, UH, WHAT DO
Y'ALL CALL IT? A-A BARRISTER?

36:37.891 --> 36:39.980
-DON'T Y'ALL NEVER
COME DOWN HERE AGAIN!

36:40.110 --> 36:41.373
YOU HEAR ME?!
-UHH.

36:41.503 --> 36:44.158
-YOU TELL YOUR FOLKS,
YOU STAY UP THERE.

36:44.289 --> 36:45.986
YOU DON'T CAUSE NO TROUBLE.

36:46.116 --> 36:48.075
I'M TRYING TO MAKE ALL THIS
GO AWAY.

36:48.206 --> 36:51.818
NOW YOU GOT TO WORK WITH ME.

36:51.948 --> 36:53.907
WHAT'D I SAY TO YOU?

36:55.561 --> 36:58.825
-YOU SAID GOOD NIGHT
AND SWEET DREAMS.

37:00.914 --> 37:02.611
WHAT YOU SAID.

37:20.281 --> 37:23.589
-BREECE, WHY DO YOU HAVE TO GIVE
HIM SUCH A HARD TIME LIKE THAT?

37:23.719 --> 37:26.940
-'CAUSE HE'S A DRUNK.

37:27.070 --> 37:30.509
-LOOK, I KNOW THAT YOU'RE
ON THAT LINE EVERY MORNING,

37:30.639 --> 37:34.904
LOOKING FOR DAY WORK,
BUT THAT IS NOT WADE'S FAULT.

37:35.035 --> 37:37.733
-HIS JOB IS TO GET THEM
DOWN OFF OF THERE.

37:37.864 --> 37:39.213
AND HE DON'T SEEM TOO MOTIVATED.

37:39.344 --> 37:40.736
DID YOU SEE THE WAY
HE DEFENDED THAT GUY?

37:40.867 --> 37:43.522
-YOU DON'T REMEMBER THAT THERE'S
A REASON FOR THAT?

37:43.652 --> 37:46.307
-FARRELLS DIDN'T KILL
YOUR DADDY.

37:46.438 --> 37:49.876
BOOZE AND PILLS KILLED YOUR
DADDY, SAME AS IT'S KILLING HIM.

37:57.231 --> 37:59.755
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

38:25.085 --> 38:27.000
-THERE HE IS UP THERE!

38:27.130 --> 38:29.132
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

38:29.263 --> 38:30.525
-HEY, FARRELL!

38:32.962 --> 38:35.835
-WELL, WELL, LOOK WHO IT IS.

38:35.965 --> 38:38.838
YOU NEED A RIDE, MR. SMART-ASS?

38:38.968 --> 38:41.493
-NO, THANKS. I'M GOOD.

38:41.623 --> 38:44.365
-WHAT, YOU JUST GONNA WALK
BACK UP THAT HILL?

38:44.496 --> 38:47.325
-I DONE IT BEFORE.
-NOT TONIGHT.

38:47.455 --> 38:49.675
-LOOK, GUYS, YOU REALLY
DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.

38:52.765 --> 38:55.724
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:55.855 --> 38:58.161
[ GRUNTING ]

38:58.292 --> 39:00.120
-HEY, HEY, HEY!

39:04.211 --> 39:06.256
-COME ON! GET HIM, JAKE!

39:06.387 --> 39:09.434
-HEY, FARRELL,
WE GOT A MESSAGE FOR YOU.

39:09.564 --> 39:10.696
-[ GROANS ]

39:10.826 --> 39:13.351
-SOMETHING YOU CAN
TAKE TO YOUR KIN.

39:13.481 --> 39:15.309
-[ GRUNTS ]
-[ LAUGHS ]

39:15.440 --> 39:19.400
YEAH! WHOO! COME ON! DO IT!

39:19.531 --> 39:20.967
DO IT!
-AAH!

39:26.189 --> 39:29.323
-YOU WANNA SEND ME A MESSAGE?
HUH?

39:29.454 --> 39:30.759
HUH?!

39:30.890 --> 39:32.544
GET BACK!
YOU WANT TO SEND ME A MESSAGE?!

39:33.501 --> 39:34.807
-AAH!

39:34.937 --> 39:37.331
-THERE'S MY MESSAGE.

39:37.462 --> 39:39.681
LEAVE US FARRELLS ALONE.

39:39.812 --> 39:41.379
[ CROWBAR CLANKS ]
[ PANTING ]

39:41.509 --> 39:44.251
-JAKE. COME ON, COME ON.
GET HIM UP.

39:44.382 --> 39:46.340
YEAH, COME ON. DAMN!

39:51.824 --> 39:54.783
[ TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ]

40:22.463 --> 40:23.638
-[ EXHALES ]

40:23.769 --> 40:26.859
[ GUN COCKS ]

40:26.989 --> 40:30.602
-DON'T YOU MOVE, BOY,
UNLESS YOU WANT TO DIE.

40:37.130 --> 40:39.741
I DON'T WANT NO TROUBLE NOW.

40:39.872 --> 40:41.743
YOU HEAR ME?

40:46.748 --> 40:50.230
-YOU KILLED MY BABY BROTHER.

40:50.360 --> 40:52.798
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

40:52.928 --> 40:57.977
-THAT NIGHT
WE ALL CAME DOWN HERE.

40:58.107 --> 41:02.285
HE WAS ONLY 8 YEARS OLD.

41:02.416 --> 41:06.986
-WELL, I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

41:07.116 --> 41:10.250
BUT WE HAVE A RIGHT TO DEFEND
OURSELVES FROM Y'ALL.

41:10.380 --> 41:11.860
GIT!

41:15.777 --> 41:17.518
[ GUNSHOT ]

41:17.649 --> 41:21.479
[ GROANING ]

41:22.915 --> 41:24.612
[ GASPING ]
[ Strained voice ] HELP ME.

41:24.743 --> 41:28.877
[ GROANS, MUTTERS ]

41:30.575 --> 41:34.753
[ GASPING ]

41:36.232 --> 41:37.973
[ BREATHING STOPS ]

42:10.658 --> 42:12.834
-[ COUGHS ]

42:12.965 --> 42:15.663
-HOW'D IT GO DOWN THERE?

42:15.794 --> 42:18.971
NOT TOO GOOD FROM THE LOOKS
OF IT. [ LAUGHS ]

42:19.101 --> 42:23.932
I TOLD YOU, BOY, THIS IS A JOB
FOR THE LOYAL AND THE TRUE,

42:24.063 --> 42:27.370
NOT A CHILD WHO DOESN'T KNOW
WHO HE IS YET.

42:49.784 --> 42:54.572
-I TRIED. [ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

42:54.702 --> 42:57.226
-AND?

42:57.357 --> 43:01.187
-WE'RE IN A WAR, G'WIN.

43:01.317 --> 43:03.537
-LOOKS LIKE
WE'RE LOSING ALREADY.

43:04.930 --> 43:06.627
-[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

43:17.856 --> 43:19.814
[ GASPS ]

43:42.271 --> 43:44.622
-I KNOW YOU'RE NOT MARRIED,
BUT I --

43:44.752 --> 43:46.580
-BUT WHAT?
YOU'VE BEEN AWAY TOO LONG.

43:46.711 --> 43:48.234
YOU'VE FORGOTTEN
HOW WE DO THINGS UP HERE.

43:59.375 --> 44:02.248
♪♪

44:06.731 --> 44:09.516
-HEY, FA, YOU HOME?

44:19.874 --> 44:22.790
♪♪
